title: Understanding Duplicate Sheets
text: When you make a copy of a sheet, it can be confusing to identify which is the original and which is the copy. Consider renaming one to avoid any mix-up.

title: Adding New Sheets
text: When you create a new sheet, it often helps to assign a name that represents the data or purpose it serves. This makes it easier to locate later.

title: Re-ordering Sheets
text: Re-arranging the sequence of sheets does not always necessitate renaming them, unless their order affects their content or context.
